{"title_page": "Alexandros Galitsios", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name= Alexandros Galitsios\n| image = \n| height = {{height|m=1.91}}\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1993|04|20|df=yes}} \n| birth_place = [[Larissa]], Greece\n| currentclub = [[Podosfairikos Omilos Xylotymbou 2006|P.O. Xylotymbou]]\n| clubnumber = 5\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]]\n| youthyears1= 2008\n| youthclubs1 = [[AEL 1964 FC|AEL U21]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs1 = [[AE Larissa FC|AEL]] \n| caps1 = 6\n| goals1 = 0 \n| years2 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2 = [[Tyrnavos 2005 F.C.|Tyrnavos 2005]] \n| caps2 = 3\n| goals2 = 0 \n| years3 = 2014\n| clubs3 = [[Dotieas Agia F.C.|Dotieas Agia]] \n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0 \n| years4 = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs4 = [[P.A.O. Krousonas F.C.|PAO Krousonas]] \n| caps4 = 0\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs5 = [[Sparta F.C.|Sparta]]\n| caps5  = 25\n| goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2017\n| clubs6 = [[Trikala F.C.|Trikala]]\n| caps6  = 0\n| goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2017\u20132019\n| clubs7 = [[Volos FC|Volos]]\n| caps7  = 24\n| goals7 = 3\n| years8 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs8 = [[Podosfairikos Omilos Xylotymbou 2006|P.O. Xylotymbou]]\n| caps8  = 18\n| goals8 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2011\n| nationalteam1 = [[Greece national under-19 football team|Greece U19]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 8\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = 7 March 2020\n}}\n  \n'''Alexandros Galitsios''' ({{lang-el|\u0391\u03bb\u03ad\u03be\u03b1\u03bd\u03b4\u03c1\u03bf\u03c2 \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03bb\u03af\u03c4\u03c3\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2}}, born 20 April 1993) is a Greek professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Cypriot Second Division]] club [[Podosfairikos Omilos Xylotymbou 2006|P.O. Xylotymbou]].\n\n==Club career==\nGalitsios started playing with the team's youth squad, on June 2008. After having several successful appearances in the U-21 championship, he was promoted to the first team on January 2012, having signed a 4,5-years contract .He made his professional debut on 9 May 2012, against [[Panthrakikos F.C.|Panthrakikos]], under manager [[Michalis Ziogas]].\n\n==International career==\nGalitsios is an active international player for Greece [[Greece national under-17 football team|U-17]] and [[Greece national under-19 football team|U-19]] teams. He made his international U-19 debut on 3 September 2011, on a friendly match against [[Sweden national under-19 football team|Sweden]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is the youngest son of the team's former captain and all-time appearances record holder [[Giannis Galitsios]], and brother of [[Georgios Galitsios|Giorgos Galitsios]], who has also played in the team for several years and is now playing for [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|KSC Lokeren]] in the [[Belgian Pro League]].\n\n==Honours==\n;Sparta\n*[[Gamma Ethniki]]: [[2015\u201316 Gamma Ethniki#Group 3|2015\u201316]]\n\n;Volos\n*[[Gamma Ethniki]]: [[2017\u201318 Gamma Ethniki#Group 4|2017\u201318]]\n*[[Football League (Greece)|Football League]]: [[2018\u201319 Football League (Greece)|2018\u201319]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.ael1964.gr/omada/amyntikoi/alexandros-galitsios AEL 1964 FC Official]\n*[https://archive.is/20130217161352/http://www.flnews.gr/teams/ael/item/3959-%CE%B5%CF%80%CE%B1%CE%B3%CE%B3%CE%B5%CE%BB%CE%BC%CE%B1%CF%84%CE%AF%CE%B1%CF%82-%CE%BF-%CE%B3%CE%BA%CE%B1%CE%BB%CE%AF%CF%84%CF%83%CE%B9%CE%BF%CF%82.html Professional Contract]\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerway}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120717132525/http://www.sportlarissa.gr/1-%CE%B1%CE%B5%CE%BB-1964/%CF%80%CE%B1%CE%B5-%CE%B1%CE%B5%CE%BB-1964/1361-%CF%80%CE%B5%CF%81%CE%AF%CE%BC%CE%B5%CE%BD%CE%B1-%CE%BA%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%81%CF%8C-%CE%BC%CE%B9%CE%B1-%CE%B5%CF%85%CE%BA%CE%B1%CE%B9%CF%81%CE%AF%CE%B1.html Debut Interview]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AsTst1-3U8w Video & Photos on Youtube]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n\n{{DEFAUL